The National Taskforce on Prohibition of Illegal Importation/Smuggling of Arms, Ammunition, Light Weapons and Pipeline Vandalism (NATFORCE) has distanced itself from one Otunba Adegbenro Adejare, saying that “he is not its spokesperson.” The Director-General of NATFORCE, Dr Baba Mohammed was quoted in a statement signed by the spokesperson of the organization as saying, the “interview recently granted by Otunba Adejare Adegbenro to sunnewsonline does not represent the position of the agency. It could be recalled that Adegbenro who granted an interview on the state of the nation recently and spoke about the level of insecurity in the country. While reacting to the development, NATFORCE spokesperson in a statement made available to newsmen and authorised by the DG said “Adegbenro is not the spokesperson and he is not authorized to grant an interview on behalf of the agency. “We acknowledge and align with the present administration’s efforts in the fight against terrorism and other forms of crimes and criminality. “The general public is advised to ignore all that came from Adegbenro.”